      "content": "that's just the official line though. if you look at the actual timestamps for the telemetry feeds during the Apollo 11 descent, there are massive chunks of data that are just... gone. or they're heavily redacted. why would they need to redact standard scientific telemetry from a successful mission unless something unexpected happened on the surface that they weren't prepared to explain to the public? it feels like there's a massive gap between what was seen on the lunar surface and what was released to the press.",
